data:
T1: Tumor size is 2 cm or less in greatest dimension and has not spread to the chest wall or skin
T2: Tumor size is more than 2 cm but not more than 5 cm in greatest dimension or tumor has invaded the chest wall or skin
T3: Tumor is more than 5 cm in greatest dimension
T4: Tumor of any size with direct extension to the chest wall and/or skin
T4a: Extension to the chest wall, not including only the superficial skin
T4b: Ulceration and/or edema (including peau d'orange) of the skin of the breast or satellite skin nodules confined to the same breast
T4c: Both T4a and T4b
T4d: Inflammatory carcinoma
